SUBSTITUTE FOR
HOUSE BILL NO. 4223
A bill to amend 1976 PA 451, entitled
"The revised school code,"
(MCL 380.1 to 380.1852) by adding section 1308g.
THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF MICHIGAN ENACT:
1 Sec. 1308g. (1) Beginning with the 2026-2027 school year, the
2 governing body of a public school or, subject to subsection (2),
3 the governing body of a nonpublic school shall develop or adopt,
4 and implement, a school safety and security training plan as
5 described in section 1308f, and shall ensure that school resource
6 officers placed in the public school or nonpublic school, school
7 safety or security personnel who work at or for the public school
8 or nonpublic school, members of a crisis response team described in
9 section 1308b, and all school staff of the public school or
CRM H00075'25 (H-2) ejt2x1

2
1 nonpublic school complete the training described in section 1308f,
2 as applicable.
3 (2) The governing body of a nonpublic school may elect to
4 exempt the nonpublic school from the requirements of this section.
5 Enacting section 1. This amendatory act does not take effect
6 unless all of the following bills of the 103rd Legislature are
7 enacted into law.
8 (a) House Bill No. 4222.
9 (b) House Bill No. 4315.
